CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 24, 1959, pg. B6, reads: "Planning Salute to Carver - A committee of prominent Pittsburghers, which met recently to draft plans for the local observance of George Washington Carver Week, Jan. 3-9, 1960, included, front row, left to right: Mrs. Goldie Hamilton, Dr. H. O. Pregler, Miss Marie A. Saul, Mrs. Alma Illery; second row: H. H. Henius, Dr. Iris L. Fike, Mmes. W. J. Moncrief, Irene Hoggans and W. C. Eichenlaub. G. Harold Griffin is standing in rear. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Women and men, including Goldie Hamilton, Dr. H. O. Pregler, Marie A. Saul, H. H. Henius, Dr. Iris L. Fike, W. J. Moncrief, G. Harold Griffin, Irene Hoggans, and W. C. Eichenlaub, seated in art classroom
